 1999-21251999-11-300,  ,  ,  HEALTH, 
PrecisRe-appointment, effective February 20, 2000, of JOEL HIRSCH WEINER, of Edmonton, Alberta, as a member of the Medical Research Council to hold office during pleasure for a term of six months, or until such time as the legislation establishing the Canadian Institutes of Health Research comes into force and the Medical Research Council is disolved, should this occur prior to the expiry of his term.
Attachments
precis:
Re-appointment, effective February 20, 2000, of JOEL HIRSCH WEINER, of
Edmonton, Alberta, as a member of the Medical Research Council to hold
office during pleasure for a term of six months, or until such time as
the legislation establishing the Canadian Institutes of Health Research
comes into force and the Medical Research Council is disolved, should
this occur prior to the expiry of his term.
